the civil aviation authority today said it was 
investigating a near collision between an air uk passenger 
airplane and an unidentified light aircraft 
the two planes passed within 200 feet of one another over 
suffolk the easternmost county in england on thursday night the 
authority said 
the pilot of the air uk plane filed a complaint after landing 
at stansted airport 60 miles southeast of london on a flight from 
paris the plane carried 17 people 
the authority said it was the 28th reported near collision over 
britain in the last four months 
