news conference in abu dhabi that iran would participate in direct 
talks if perez de cuellar asked it to 
here is where the un talks stand now 
points of agreement 
both sides unconditionally accept resolution 598 a 10point 
plan including an immediate ceasefire and troop withdrawal a 
prisoner exchange formal peace talks and a commission to determine 
which side was the aggressor in the war 
both agreed to hold immediate separate talks with the 
secretarygeneral on implementing the resolution they agree the 
secretarygeneral will set dates for the different phases of the 
plan 
a team of un military experts has visited both capitals to 
work out details of a ceasefire and another is investigating 
prisonerofwar issues in both countries 
points of disagreement 
iraq insists on direct talks in new york before a ceasefire 
while iran rejects direct talks at this time 
iraq also demands that before a ceasefire goes into effect 
iran promise not to attack iraqi and neutral shipping in the 
persian gulf it also calls for the united nations to dredge the 
disputed shatt alarab waterway the southern boundary between the 
two nations 
iran will make no commitments on these issues 
