ceremony at the great hall of the people in which more than 80000 
military veterans received medals 
the military reforms are the work of deng xiaoping maos 
successor as chinas top leader and head of the central military 
commission deng was not present at saturdays ceremony 
deng 84 has abandoned maos concept of a massive peasant army 
and sought to turn the peoples liberation army into a streamlined 
wellequipped and modern fighting force 
in the past few years he has reduced the worlds largest army 
from 4 million to 3 million concentrated on developing modern 
weapons systems and pushed for the reinstatement of ranks 
the restoration of ranks and the awarding of medals banned by 
mao in 1965 is an effort to boost army morale when the military 
has been overshadowed in chinas push for economic modernization 
under the reforms military officers in the army are to be 
divided into three grades with 11 ranks there will be four ranks 
of generals four ranks of field officer senior colonel colonel 
lieutenant colonel and major and three ranks of company officer 
captain lieutenant and second lieutenant 
