the colonys harbor to erskine camp the third temporary detention 
center for the boat people 
the new policy provides that the vietnamese be kept in those 
centers until vietnam agrees to take them back 
boat people who arrived before the new policy took effect are 
still eligible for resettlement they are kept in refugee centers 
separate from the detention centers for recent arrivals 
all boat people arriving after june 15 are considered illegal 
immigrants subject to repatriation unless they can prove they fled 
persecution in communist vietnam the hong kong government 
previously considered all boat people refugees eligible for 
resettlement 
